A polio immunisation campaign is underway in four African countries. Africa was declared free of wild poliovirus in 2020. But Malawi detected a case in February.  eNCA speaks to UNICEF Eastern and Southern Africa's Dr Saumya Anand for more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Africa was declared free of wild poliovirus in 2020. However, Malawi detected a case in February. Now more than 9 million children are to be vaccinated in East and Southern Africa. Three more rounds of vaccinations will follow in the coming months, covering a total of more than 20 million children. Watch the vide above for more details on this story.